1. Deterministic gate PASSED — ran `bash plugins/cool-workflow/scripts/release-gate.sh` myself: build clean, full `npm test` green, substance/test-evidence/cadence/branch-naming all pass; wrote gate-<sha>.ok.
2. No spec accretion — every new/modified type field in v0.1.76..HEAD is read by a runtime module in the same range:
   - WorkflowTaskDefinition.{label,model,agentType,schema} + WorkflowPhaseDefinition.mode carried into RunTask/RunPhase at orchestrator/lifecycle-operations.ts:90,461-466.
   - phase.mode read in drive.ts:470 (autoWidth → concurrent round); task.model drive.ts:203; task.agentType drive.ts:193,226,366; task.schema verifier.ts:52-53; task.label drive.ts:246.
   - limits.tokenBudget enforced drive.ts:152; requireAttestedTelemetry worker-isolation.ts:392 + agent-config.ts; AgentDelegationInput.{reportedUsage,usageSignature,usageTrustPublicKey} worker-isolation.ts:381-383; preparedAgentOutcome/AgentChildOutcome execution-backend.ts:1133-1134; WorkerManifest.{scopePath,manifestPath,retryCount} worker-isolation.ts:208,220,76.
3. Tests are revert-sensitive, not trivial:
   - token-budget-enforcement-smoke.js drives a real run, sets budget=1, asserts status "blocked" with reason "6 recorded tokens >= budget 1" and that the accepted hop stays recorded.
   - one-way-boundary-smoke.js invokes the repo's tsc on a negative callable fixture AND the real envelope+smuggled-client fixture (must NOT compile, matching "does not satisfy the constraint"), with a positive control that must compile.
   - concurrent-failure-semantics-smoke.js runs 16 agents with hang+crash+dirty, asserting wall-clock far below the ~36s serial floor and deterministic record order.
